  "essence": "Correlations between internal components and observed capabilities do not identify causal responsibility, obstructing reliable attribution and targeted model editing.",
  "paraphrases": {
    "LLM_NLP": "Component-level attribution in large language models fails when correlations between attention heads and token predictions are treated as causal; distributed effects across the KV cache and long context length obscure which heads actually implement the capability, so component-level edits can degrade perplexity.",
    "MULTIMODAL": "In vision–language models, cross-modal alignment statistics between visual tokens and text do not establish which query-conditioned attention pathways causally drive grounding; entanglement within the image embedding obscures responsibility, hindering reliable VQA accuracy attribution.",
