  "method": "Define a component family and an interventional knob. Choose a granular basis to probe (e.g., SAE features, MLP neurons, attention heads, or low-rank subspaces). For each component c, implement a parametric intervention I(c; α) that scales, nulls, or injects activation with a signed strength α. Calibrate α per component to achieve a fixed target KL divergence δ between the model’s clean and intervened token distributions, so all components are compared at equal perturbation strength. For any capability of interest, specify a measurable scorer (unit tests or a judge LLM) and a token-level Component Dependency Measure that compares p(y_t | history, I off) and p(y_t | history, I on) under the calibrated δ; aggregate per-token effects into capability-specific scores.\n\nActively harvest diagnostic contexts that maximize causal signal. Starting from seed prompts that elicit the capability, run a search loop that proposes context mutations (paraphrases, harder variants, distractors) and selects those where the calibrated intervention on any candidate component yields large, reliable output divergences or capability score deltas. Interleave model runs with selection to concentrate the diagnostic set on regions where causal effects are identifiable, not merely correlated. This planner-style data collection increases power and reduces confounding by ensuring comparisons are made where the capability is actually exercised.\n\nEstimate causal responsibility with knockout–rescue tests and robust aggregation. For each component, compute calibrated knockout effects on the diagnostic set and confirm directionality via anti-interventions (amplify vs suppress). Perform rescue by injecting a downstream surrogate signal to test whether the observed impairment is specifically mediated by the targeted pathway. Quantify redundancy and synergy via pairwise and small-set ablations; fit a minimal hitting set of components whose joint knockout flips the capability metric, and estimate marginal contributions with greedy Shapley-style approximations. Aggregate effect sizes across contexts with heavy-tailed estimators (e.g., Student’s t regression or median-of-means) and report confidence intervals via bootstrap, yielding a ranked list of causally responsible components and minimal causal cores.\n\nEdit within a trust region. Attach light-weight gates to the identified components (scalars or tiny MLPs) and optimize them to attenuate or enhance the capability on the diagnostic set while enforcing a per-batch KL budget to the original model, preserving global behavior. Use a trust-region update that maximizes the desired capability objective (or minimizes an undesired one) under the KL constraint; stop early when the capability change saturates or the KL budget is met. Validate on held-out contexts, and, if needed, widen edits by adding or removing components from the causal core based on post-edit re-scoring.\n\nProduce output-grounded interpretations. For each causally identified component, automatically summarize its function by collecting tokens and behaviors whose probabilities most increase or decrease under calibrated interventions on the diagnostic set, clustering them, and prompting a judge model to produce concise hypotheses. Track the component dependency curves over generation steps to reveal when and how the capability is mediated. Package each component with: its effect size and CI, minimal counterfactual examples demonstrating knockout–rescue, the learned gate value if edited, and a natural-language description tied to its downstream impacts.",
  "rationale": "Causality requires interventions and counterfactuals, not correlations. By calibrating per-component interventions to a fixed KL distance, we obtain fair, comparable effect sizes across heterogeneous units and avoid over-penalizing sensitive layers. The active context search focuses measurement on cases where the capability is engaged, increasing statistical power and reducing spurious associations. Knockout–rescue tests and small-set ablations distinguish direct mediators from passengers and reveal redundancy, while robust aggregation prevents a few outlier prompts from dominating conclusions.\n\nFor editing, KL-constrained, trust-region gating provides local, controllable changes to the identified causal pathways while guarding against off-target drift. Output-based summaries convert raw effect measurements into human-usable interpretations, grounding component descriptions in their demonstrable downstream consequences rather than input correlations. Together, these steps reliably identify which components causally implement a capability and turn that knowledge into targeted, safe edits and clear interpretations.",
